headline: Adobe Stock Gets an Upgrade. It’s ‘Fairly Valued’ Now.
summary: Adobe  stock keeps getting beat up, but a KeyBanc Capital Markets analyst doesn’t recommend selling it anymore.  On Friday, Jackson Ader upgraded shares of the creative software company to Sector Weight from Underweight.  Midday, the stock was down 0.8 to $386.55.
